{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020", // modern JS target
    "module": "commonjs", // WebdriverIO uses CommonJS modules
    "checkJs": true, // enables type checking in JS files
    "baseUrl": ".", // root directory of the project
    "paths": {
      "*": [
        "node_modules/*",
        "src/*"
      ] // resolve modules from node_modules and your src folder
    },
    "allowJs": true, // allow JS files to be compiled (for type checking)
    "moduleResolution": "node", // resolve modules like Node.js
    "resolveJsonModule": true, // allow importing json files
    "types": [
      "node",
      "@wdio/cucumber-framework",
      "expect-webdriverio",
      "@wdio/globals",
      "@wdio/types"
    ] // add typings for node, webdriverio, and cucumber
  },
  "include": [
    "src/**/*.js",
    "wdio.conf.js",
    "node_modules/expect-webdriverio"
  ],
  "exclude": [
    "node_modules"
  ]
}
/**This configuration file is used to provide type checking and module resolution for a WebdriverIO project using Cucumber and JavaScript.
 It specifies the compiler options, including the target ECMAScript version, module system, and paths for module resolution.
 The `include` section specifies which files to include for type checking, while the `exclude` section excludes the `node_modules` directory.
 The configuration is designed to work with WebdriverIO's async/await syntax and Cucumber step definitions.
 It also allows for importing JSON files and provides type definitions for Node.js, WebdriverIO, and Cucumber.
 **/